## 2) A Docker image builds successfully, but the container exits immediately after starting. What will you do?

**Answer:**\
I first check the container logs:

    docker logs <container_id>

Then I inspect the container configuration:

    docker inspect <container_id>

After that I verify:

-   whether the startup command is correct\
-   whether required environment variables are passed\
-   whether the application process is crashing\
-   whether dependencies are missing\
-   whether the app is binding to the expected port

If needed, I run the image interactively:

    docker run -it <image_name> sh

Common reasons are wrong CMD, missing env variables, application crash,
or dependency/configuration issues.

