## 4) Your pod is in CrashLoopBackOff. How do you handle it?

**Answer:**\
I handle it in this order:

1.  check logs\

```{=html}
<!-- -->
```
    kubectl logs <pod-name>

2.  check previous logs if restarting quickly\

```{=html}
<!-- -->
```
    kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous

3.  describe the pod\

```{=html}
<!-- -->
```
    kubectl describe pod <pod-name>

4.  verify environment variables\
5.  verify ConfigMaps and Secrets\
6.  verify startup command\
7.  test connectivity to dependencies like database or API\
8.  check resource limits and probe failures

Typical causes are application startup failure, missing configuration,
DB connection failure, or OOMKilled.

