## 5) Users say the application is down, but pods are showing as Running. What could be wrong?

**Answer:**\
A pod being in Running state does not always mean the application is
healthy. I check:

-   readiness probe status\
-   application logs\
-   service endpoints\
-   service selector and pod labels\
-   ingress/load balancer config\
-   whether app is listening on correct port/interface

Commands:

    kubectl get pods
    kubectl get svc
    kubectl get endpoints
    kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
    kubectl logs <pod-name>

Very often the app is running but not ready, or the service is not
routing traffic to it.

