## 6) A deployment succeeded, but the old version of the application is still visible. Why?

**Answer:**\
Possible reasons include:

-   image tag reused, such as latest\
-   image was not pulled again\
-   wrong deployment updated\
-   wrong namespace\
-   browser cache or CDN cache\
-   rollout not triggered properly

I verify with:

    kubectl describe deployment <deployment-name>
    kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
    kubectl rollout history deployment/<deployment-name>

Best practice is to use unique image tags like build number or commit
SHA instead of latest.

