## 7) Your Jenkins server disk is full. How do you respond?

**Answer:**\
First I confirm usage:

    df -h
    du -sh /var/lib/jenkins/*
    docker system df

Then I identify the heavy areas:

-   old workspaces\
-   build history\
-   archived artifacts\
-   Docker images and containers\
-   logs

Actions:

-   delete old workspaces/builds\
-   configure retention policy\
-   prune unused Docker images\
-   rotate logs\
-   offload artifacts to S3 or artifact repository

I also make sure to implement cleanup policies so the issue doesn't
repeat.

