## 8) Your application is exposed through Ingress, but users are getting 502 Bad Gateway. What do you check?

**Answer:**\
A 502 usually means the ingress controller cannot reach a healthy
backend. I check:

-   backend pod health\
-   service configuration\
-   service endpoints\
-   ingress rules\
-   backend app port\
-   readiness probe\
-   ingress controller logs

Commands:

    kubectl get ingress
    kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name>
    kubectl get svc
    kubectl get endpoints
    kubectl logs <backend-pod>

If service has no endpoints or backend is unhealthy, ingress will return
502.

