## 9) You deployed a new release and now CPU usage is very high. What would you do?

**Answer:**\
First I determine whether the issue is application-side or
infrastructure-side.

Checks:

-   compare with previous version\
-   check logs for loops/errors\
-   inspect traffic spike\
-   inspect pod resource usage\
-   inspect node usage

Commands:

    kubectl top pod
    kubectl top node
    kubectl logs <pod-name>
    top
    htop

If the new version caused the problem, I would rollback quickly while
investigating the root cause.

