## 10) A Kubernetes pod cannot connect to MongoDB. How do you troubleshoot?

**Answer:**\
I verify the full path of connectivity:

1.  correct hostname?\
2.  correct port?\
3.  service exists?\
4.  endpoints exist?\
5.  DNS resolves?\
6.  credentials correct?\
7.  DB pod/service healthy?

Commands:

    kubectl get svc
    kubectl get endpoints
    kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- sh
    nslookup mongodb-service
    nc -zv mongodb-service 27017

I also check Secrets and application environment variables because wrong
credentials or wrong service name is very common.

