## 11) One of the containers is restarting repeatedly because of OOMKilled. What will you do?

**Answer:**\
OOMKilled means the container exceeded its memory limit. I check:

    kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
    kubectl top pod

Then I verify:

-   memory limits and requests\
-   application memory usage pattern\
-   memory leak possibility\
-   whether runtime settings need tuning

Short-term fix may be increasing memory limit. Long-term fix is
application tuning if the memory growth is abnormal.

