## 19) A new engineer accidentally deleted a working container. What do you do?

**Answer:**\
If the container was created from an image, I simply recreate it from
the same image and configuration.

If persistent data was stored only inside that container and no volume
was used, data may be lost.

That is why persistent data should always use volumes or external
managed storage.

